text: Thet Htar Thuzar (; born 15 March 1999) is a Burmese badminton player. She participated at the 2013 Southeast Asian Games in her home country Myanmar. She won her first International title at the Egypt International 2018. In 2019 she has reached eight finals, most in the African Badminton Circuit, winning 6 events (in Uganda, Kenya, Mauritius, Benin, Ivory Coast and again in Egypt) == Achievements == === BWF International Challenge/Series (8 titles, 3 runners- up) === Women's singles {| class="sortable wikitable" style="font-size: 90%;" !
